The Port Elizabeth International Airport will conduct a safety exercise today with various stakeholdersPicture: Chris Dorney / 123RF
The Port Elizabeth International Airport will conduct a safety exercise today with various stakeholders.
Airports Company South Africa said the exercise would consist of a full-scale aircraft simulation at the Noordhoek Ski Boat Club involving emergency vehicles and personnel responding to a simulated emergency situation.


Residents are advised that certain areas will be affected by traffic disruptions.
The roads affected include Marine Drive, Admiralty Way, Strandfontein Road, La Roche Drive, Driftsands Drive and Walmer Boulevard.
Road users and travellers are advised to use alternative routes to avoid delays. – Herald Reporter.


